As a general rule, iniuria to A would not affect B unless it was so intended ; but where the relation between the two was intimate, and such as to have been known to the delinquent, the intention was presumcd: ‘maritus in uxoris pudore, pater in existimatione filiarum propriam iniuriam pati intelleguntur' Cod. 9. 35. 2.
